rComments: Super passionate and inspirational lecturer! His knowledge of the subject matter runs deep and he really cares how the students learn and offers plenty of help outside class hours. Would love to sit in on more advanced lecture topics/courses of his.

super sweet prof I like how he actually explains the course and is willing to explain things multiple times until we all understand. Class was really interesting and the midterms / exam is stressful when preparing but once u write it it is pretty easy. he always says before taking a test "it is more intimidating than difficult!" which i found true

Prof Atytalla is a really fantastic professor. he is not only a caring and understanding professor but also conveys the material of his lectures in his courses in an interesting and fun way. Lecture heavy, his grading is very fair, provides great review material. I really enjoyed this class even as someone who is not in philosophy or arts.

Would absolutely not recommend taking his classes. Class grade is based on two tests worth 30% each and a final of 40%. All his lectures consist of solely quotes which is not helpful what so ever. Pretty much have to teach yourself all the material.

Such a sweet prof - when I took him, he was doing his PhD and was super nervous as he was a new prof, but that just made me want to give him even more of my attention. He picks the topics you cover in the class and they are super interesting.

Marks are given generously. He gave study guides ripped straight from the exams so even though there are only a few evaluations they are easy if you just use what he gives you. Listen to the lectures easy A.

He's a great guy and cares a lot, but sometimes the content is really boring and repetitive. The content is super specific but open book so his slides come in handy. If you understand the content, easy A - if you don't, good luck passing. Readings are dense and boring but can go off the slides w/o reading them. 2 midterms, 1 final. Marks late.
teacherRatingTags: ['Graded by few things', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: I am a first-year student and can say with confidence that John Atytalla was by far the most considerate and caring professor I have had. There were two situations that occurred for me in this course and both times he responded quickly to my email and once gave a call to clear things up. Philosophy is a hard class but with john it was amazing.

Easily one of the best professors I've had. His lectures are easy to follow considering that philosophy can be hard. He's passionate and very nice. His tests are straightforward if you pay attention to his lectures.

Literally the best professor I've ever had. He gives you flexibility on tests so you can "choose" what material you best understood. For example, he'll give you 10 questions and you pick 6 to answer. He speaks well, is professional, is very understanding, and I respect him so much. He's a young prof and he connected really well with us. Do it!

You basically have to teach yourself the content. The slideshows are all white pasted with text- mostly quotes (remember how in high school how we were told NOT to do that... ironic). Just such a boring class. I never went because I'd fall asleep which explains why I'm getting approx. C's. I would avoid taking this class.
Really cool and fair Prof. The course isn't necessarily easy but he's always ready to help and available for office hours.

Amazing prof. Engaging lecturer, cute, humble, extraordinarily professional. He's not an 'easy' prof in that you won't get away with skipping and learning nothing, but if you engage, do the readings, come to class, and show up asking for help he will go the extra mile for you in his office hours. 10/10
His slides were not that clear and he used quotes a lot. The textbook for this class was huge and not worth the price when we only covered a little of the book in comparison to the whole thing.

Great, amazing prof. One of the best of my first year at uOttawa. Super prof, and his exams are extremely straightforward and are very lecture and textbook based. Lectures are clarifications of the textbook readings, so if you do the readings and study them you should get an easy A. Overall, great prof, youre lucky if you get him.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Graded by few things', 'Caring']

rComments: To pass exams you actually have to understand the material and be able to apply it to real life examples, but professor Atytalla gives you all the resources to do this. He is really interesting to listen to and gets super involved in class discussions. Lectures can be a bit boring depending on your interest in the topic, but I overall recommend it.
teacherRatingTags: ['Gives good feedback', 'Lecture heavy', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: He helps when you need the help and during class his lectures are with much enthusiasm; doesn't make you fall asleep but to come to class.

John is genuinely cool. Unlike some professors, he's not cool because he has snapchat. He's cool because he's passionate, he dresses like a retro professor, he sometime longboards to class, wants to hear form his students and wants to help, and he is just grade A cool. He is great and I will take his classes any chance I can get!

His love for philosophy is what made this class so enjoyable. He really cares about his students and can connect with them on deeper levels than just the subject at hand. What's learned in the class is super interesting and can be used in every day life too - makes going to class easier... plus the fact he's a real looker

First year teacher, a little scatterbrained but you can tell he really cares. He's very helpful as long as you put in the time outside of class if you find the course matter difficult. I look forward to his classes every week, great discussions and his enthusiasm for the topic is infectious.
First year teaching. First week or so was a little rough, but he really tries hard and it is paying off. I really enjoy his lectures and look forward to them every week. Take his classes if you can.
